10-12 birds in an intense interaction, not visible at times; a few physical attacks or chases, but not all that much overt aggression; 3-8 m up in dense, viney, disturbed forest patch amongst shade coffee forest; afer the wonderfully intense period ends at 6:00, intermittent isolated calls that are clearer in a way;
two birds 12 m up in the subcanopy of forest;
pair, male doing longer, louder but both vocalizing; 2-5 m up in viny tangles; loudest, most interesting from 1:19 to 3:13;

interval shortened at 0:59 and 2:22; a few loud songs, but mostly very quiet, 'conversational' songs/interaction calls among three birds inside a viny tangle in a large TDF tree; no overt hostilities among them;
not seen; from inside a mango orchard; different from those recorded earlier; includes some rather quiet vocalizations;
calls from four birds working through TDF at medium height; good trogon vocalizations, but much else going on at the same time; interval altered at 5:42, 6:05, and 7:02;
